  "lessons": [
    {
      "id": "les_ppb_crr",
      "moduleId": "m_ppb_a",
      "title": {
        "en": "Cash Reserve Ratio & SLR"
      },
      "estMinutes": 5,
      "version": 1,
      "cards": [
        {
          "id": "card_crr_intro",
          "kind": "intro",
          "blocks": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "md": {
                "en": "Banks cannot lend out all their deposited funds. By law, they must hold a portion back for security. Two ratios dictate these requirements."
              }
            }
          ],
          "srsEligible": false
        },
        {
          "id": "card_crr_concept",
          "kind": "concept",
          "blocks": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "md": {
                "en": "**Cash Reserve Ratio (CRR)**: The percentage of demand and time deposits that banks must keep as cash reserves **with the RBI**. No interest is paid on these funds."
              }
            },
            {
              "kind": "chart",
              "spec": {
                "type": "bar_segment",
                "total": "Total deposits",
                "segment": {
                  "label": "CRR 4.5%",
                  "value": 4.5
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "srsEligible": true
        },
        {
          "id": "card_slr_concept",
          "kind": "concept",
          "blocks": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "md": {
                "en": "**Statutory Liquidity Ratio (SLR)**: The mandatory proportion of deposits a bank must store in safe, liquid assets (gold, cash, approved bonds) **within the bank itself**."
              }
            },
            {
              "kind": "chart",
              "spec": {
                "type": "bar_segment",
                "total": "Total deposits",
                "segment": {
                  "label": "SLR 18%",
                  "value": 18
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "srsEligible": true
        },
        {
          "id": "card_crr_slr_diff",
          "kind": "example",
          "blocks": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "md": {
                "en": "CRR vs SLR contrast:\n- **CRR**: Kept as cash **with the RBI** (earns no interest).\n- **SLR**: Kept as liquid assets **by the bank** (can earn interest via government bonds)."
              }
            }
          ],
          "srsEligible": true
        },
        {
          "id": "card_crr_slr_recap",
          "kind": "recap",
          "blocks": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "md": {
                "en": "CRR reserves cash at the RBI. SLR keeps liquid assets at the bank. The RBI sets both to regulate banking liquidity and system stability."
              }
            }
          ],
          "srsEligible": false
        }
      ],
      "probeQuestionIds": [
        "q_crr_holder",
        "cs_crr_q1",
        "cs_crr_q2",
        "q_slr_assets"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "les_ppb_kyc_aml",
      "moduleId": "m_ppb_a",
      "title": {
        "en": "KYC Guidelines & Anti-Money Laundering"
      },
      "estMinutes": 5,
      "version": 1,
      "cards": [
        {
          "id": "card_kyc_intro",
          "kind": "intro",
          "blocks": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "md": {
                "en": "Banks must verify customer identities before opening accounts to prevent financial crimes. This is done through Know Your Customer (KYC) and Anti-Money Laundering (AML) rules."
              }
            }
          ],
          "srsEligible": false
        },
        {
          "id": "card_kyc_ovd",
          "kind": "concept",
          "blocks": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "md": {
                "en": "**Officially Valid Documents (OVDs)**: To open accounts, customers must provide OVDs. These are: Passport, Aadhaar, Driving License, Voter ID, NREGA job card, and Letter from National Population Register."
              }
            }
          ],
          "srsEligible": true
        },
        {
          "id": "card_aml_stages",
          "kind": "concept",
          "blocks": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "md": {
                "en": "**AML Stages**: Money laundering flows through three key steps:\n1. **Placement**: Injecting illegal cash into the formal financial system.\n2. **Layering**: Spreading money across multiple accounts/transactions to hide its origin.\n3. **Integration**: Merging clean funds back into the economy (e.g., real estate)."
              }
            }
          ],
          "srsEligible": true
        },
        {
          "id": "card_aml_example",
          "kind": "example",
          "blocks": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "md": {
                "en": "Example flow:\n- **Placement**: Depositing cash bags in small amounts in a bank.\n- **Layering**: Wire-transferring funds to shell firms overseas.\n- **Integration**: Purchasing luxury apartments using the clean bank wire."
              }
            }
          ],
          "srsEligible": true
        },
        {
          "id": "card_kyc_aml_recap",
          "kind": "recap",
          "blocks": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "md": {
                "en": "KYC verifies identity using 6 OVDs. AML stops dirty money through Placement, Layering, and Integration controls."
              }
            }
          ],
          "srsEligible": false
        }
      ],
      "probeQuestionIds": [
        "q_kyc_ovd",
        "q_aml_stages"
      ]
    }
  ],
